The Next Generation Science Assessment project (www.nextgenscienceassessment.org) is a collaboration among 
WestEd, Michigan State University, the University of Illinois Chicago, and Concord Consortium. The collaborative work 
was funded by the National Science Foundation (1853927, 1316874, 1316903, 1316908, 1903103), the Gordon and 
Betty Moore Foundation (Grant #4482), and the Chan-Zuckerberg Initiative (Grant #094374).
